F5 BIG-IP HA Pair Deployment — Nutanix AHV
==========================================

Deploys an active/standby F5 BIG-IP HA pair on Nutanix AHV using
Ansible Automation Platform (AAP) and the official nutanix.ncp collection.

MINIMUM COLLECTION VERSION
---------------------------
  nutanix.ncp >= 2.5.0   <-- REQUIRED, do not use earlier versions
  f5networks.f5_modules >= 1.28.0
  ansible.utils >= 3.0.0
  ansible.posix >= 1.5.0

Install:
  ansible-galaxy collection install -r collections/requirements.yml

WHY >= 2.5.0
-------------
  ntnx_virtual_switches_info_v2  — added in v2.5.0 (needed by nutanix_network role)
  ntnx_subnets_v2                — stable VLAN subnet CRUD (v2.5.0)
  ntnx_vms_v2                    — VM lifecycle on v4 API (v2.0.0+, improved in v2.5.0)
  ntnx_vms_power_actions_v2      — graceful shutdown in teardown (v2.5.0)

All v1 modules (ntnx_vms, ntnx_subnets, ntnx_images without _v2 suffix) are
deprecated and will be removed in Q4-CY2026. This codebase uses v2 only.

STRUCTURE
----------
  ansible.cfg                      Ansible configuration
  collections/requirements.yml     Collection dependencies
  extra_vars_aap/extra_vars.yml    All user-configurable variables
  inventory/hosts.yml              Bastion + F5 node inventory
  playbooks/
    site.yml                       Master playbook (runs all phases)
    00_nutanix_prereqs.yml         Phase 0 — PC connectivity + cluster lookup
    01_nutanix_network.yml         Phase 1 — Create VLAN subnets in Prism Central
    02_image_upload.yml            Phase 2 — Upload QCOW2 to Image Service
    03_deploy_vm.yml               Phase 3 — Deploy BIG-IP VMs on AHV
    04_onboard.yml                 Phase 4 — Install DO + Declarative Onboarding
    teardown.yml                   Reverse-order cleanup
    roles/
      nutanix_prereqs/             PC connectivity check, cluster ext_id resolution
      nutanix_network/             VLAN subnet creation via ntnx_subnets_v2
      nutanix_image_upload/        QCOW2 upload via Prism Central REST API
      f5_vm_deploy/                VM creation via ntnx_vms_v2
      f5_wait_mgmt/                Wait for BIG-IP management (platform-agnostic)
      f5_install_do/               Install DO RPM (platform-agnostic)
      f5_declarative_onboarding/   POST DO declaration (platform-agnostic)

PHASES vs OPENSHIFT EQUIVALENT
--------------------------------
  Phase 0  nutanix_prereqs      ≈  ocp_nmstate_operator (preflight)
  Phase 1  nutanix_network      ≈  ocp_node_network + ocp_prereqs (network + NADs)
  Phase 2  image_upload         ≈  f5_image_upload (CDI → Image Service)
  Phase 3  deploy_vm            ≈  f5_vm_deploy (KubeVirt VM → AHV VM)
  Phase 4  onboard              =  identical (DO is platform-agnostic)

NETWORKING
-----------
  Unlike OpenShift (which needs NMState + OVS bridges + Multus NADs),
  Nutanix manages VLAN switching natively in AHV. Phase 1 creates four
  unmanaged VLAN-backed subnets in Prism Central (no IPAM — F5 owns IPs).
  VMs attach NICs to these subnets by ext_id at creation time.

  Virtual switch (vs0 by default) is the AHV bridge anchoring subnets
  to physical uplinks. Configure via virtual_switch in f5_networks extra_vars.

REQUIRED VARIABLES (update in extra_vars_aap/extra_vars.yml)
--------------------------------------------------------------
  nutanix_host            Prism Central FQDN or IP
  nutanix_cluster_name    AHV cluster name as shown in Prism Central
  nutanix_image_name      Name for the uploaded BIG-IP image
  qcow2_filename          Filename of the QCOW2 on the CIFS share
  f5_networks             VLAN IDs, subnet names, virtual switch
  f5_license_type         regkey or bigiq
  f5_primary_node         Must match a host in inventory/hosts.yml
  f5_secondary_node       Must match a host in inventory/hosts.yml

AAP CREDENTIAL TYPES NEEDED
-----------------------------
  - Nutanix Prism Central  (custom type mapping nutanix_username/password)
  - Vault                  (cifs_username, cifs_password, f5 credentials)
  - Machine                (SSH key for bastion01)

TEARDOWN FLAGS
---------------
  bigiq_revoke_on_teardown: true   Revoke BIG-IQ licenses first
  delete_disk_image: true          Remove image from Nutanix Image Service
  delete_subnets: true             Remove VLAN subnets from Prism Central
                                   (default false — subnets may be shared)
